# . Write a program that asks the user to enter an angle between −180◦
# and 180◦. Using an # expression with the modulo operator, convert the angle to its equivalent 
# between 0◦ and 360◦
n = int(input("give an angle between -180 or 180 > "))

converted_n = (n+180) %360

if converted_n == 0:
    converted_n = 360
print(converted_n)
